{
  "stem": "7437.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I guess most of the adults realized what was happening, because I recall that my mother took all the little jewelry-- we were not rich in a sense of having much money and all, because my parents were intellectuals.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But whatever jewelry she had, she divided it and she sewed it into our clothing, outer clothing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when I asked, why are you doing that, she says, that's for a rainy day.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But right when the Germans came in, within two or three days they came around with the Ukrainians from our town, with a list of about 300 Jewish leaders, and my father among them.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They grabbed my father, didn't even give him a chance to put on a jacket.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was the last time I saw my father.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I tried to find out what happened, but I was never successful in definitely establishing what happened to my father.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "After that, for the next two weeks they rounded up the Jews in the marketplace.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we had to watch when they burned our synagogue and all the other little-- we had one main synagogue and several smaller ones.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Germans burned the synagogues.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They took out all the Torahs and all the books of prayer, and they burned that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we had to watch.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That was the beginning.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "After that, every day they came up with new decrees.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "First, we needed to bring all the silver, gold, all the price-- all the--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Valuable.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--valuables to the marketplace.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was going on every day for about two weeks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were ordered to wear a yellow star on the front of our clothing and on the back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everyone over 14 years of age was ordered to slave labor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was not 14, so I was left to myself.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
